sql:
SELECT COUNT(signal_id) 
FROM chemical_signals 
WHERE molecular_weight > (SELECT AVG(molecular_weight) FROM chemical_signals);

SELECT name, molecular_weight, boiling_point, solubility
FROM chemical_signals
WHERE molecular_weight > 0 AND boiling_point > 0 AND solubility > 0;

external_knowledge:
- "chemical signal" refers to a substance or molecule that is used for communication or other biological functions;
- "origin" refers to the source or place from which the chemical signal is derived, such as "female urine" or "male bladder urine";
- "molecular weight" is a measure of the mass of a molecule, often used to identify and characterize chemical substances;
- "boiling point" is the temperature at which a liquid turns into a vapor, and it can vary depending on the molecular structure of the substance.

sql:
SELECT name, molecular_weight
FROM chemical_signals
ORDER BY molecular_weight DESC;

